TITLE: Configuring Fixed Window Rate Limit with Custom Characteristic in Next.js
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to set up a fixed window rate limit rule with a custom characteristic 'userId' in a Next.js application using Arcjet. It limits requests to 100 per minute for each unique user ID.
SOURCE: https://github.com/arcjet/arcjet-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/rate-limiting/configuration.mdx#2025-04-12_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { Arcjet } from "@arcjet/next";

const aj = new Arcjet({
  // Your Arcjet API key
  key: process.env.ARCJET_KEY,
});

aj.rateLimit({
  name: "user-limits",
  algorithm: "fixedWindow",
  characteristics: ["userId"],
  max: 100,
  window: "1m",
});
```

