TITLE: Protecting Auth.js Route Handler in Next.js App Router
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to extend Auth.js route handler in Next.js App Router by adding Arcjet rate limiting and bot protection. It configures Arcjet to allow up to 10 requests in a 60-second window and blocks bot traffic.
SOURCE: https://github.com/arcjet/arcjet-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/integrations/authjs.mdx#2025-04-12_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import NextAuth from "next-auth";
import GitHub from "next-auth/providers/github";
import { Arcjet } from "@arcjet/next";

const handler = NextAuth({
  providers: [GitHub],
});

// Add Arcjet's rate limiting protection to the request handler
export const { GET, POST } = new Arcjet({
  key: process.env.ARCJET_KEY,
  rules: [
    {
      // Rate limit login attempts
      name: "Rate limit login attempts",
      // Only rate limit POST requests (login/logout attempts)
      when: (request) => request.method === "POST",
      // Allow 10 login attempts per minute
      rateLimit: {
        window: "60s",
        max: 10,
        characteristics: ["ip"],
      },
      // Prevent bots from logging in
      bot: {
        block: true,
      },
    },
  ],
}).protect(handler);
```

