TITLE: Implementing Custom Logging in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Example of setting up custom logging for the Arcjet SDK using Pino logger in JavaScript, with different configurations for production and development environments.
SOURCE: https://github.com/arcjet/arcjet-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/reference/sveltekit.mdx#2025-04-12_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import pino from "pino";
import arcjet, { fixedWindow } from "@arcjet/sveltekit";

const logger =
  process.env.NODE_ENV === "production"
    ? pino()
    : pino({
        transport: {
          target: "pino-pretty",
          options: {
            colorize: true,
          },
        },
      });

const aj = arcjet({
  key: process.env.ARCJET_KEY,
  characteristics: ["ip.src"],
  rules: [
    fixedWindow({
      window: "1h",
      max: 60,
    }),
  ],
  logger,
});
```

